        <section id="bottom-line" aria-labelledby="bottom-line-heading">
          <h2 id="bottom-line-heading">Overview</h2>
          <p>
            9 July is Argentina's Día de la Independencia: a winter national holiday that commemorates the declaration made in San Miguel de Tucumán on 9 July 1816 by the Congreso de Tucumán. The deputies declared the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Provinces_of_the_R%C3%ADo_de_la_Plata" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Provincias Unidas en Sud América</a> (United Provinces in South America, a polity whose claimed territory included more than modern Argentina) independent of Spain; days later they added a break with any other foreign domination (<a href="https://www.educ.ar/recursos/132481/9-de-julio-dia-de-la-declaracion-de-la-independencia" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Educ.ar</a>; <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Argentine_Declaration_of_Independence" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Acta / Wikipedia</a>). Under <a href="https://www.argentina.gob.ar/normativa/nacional/ley-27399-281835/texto" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Ley 27.399</a> (2017), the date is an immovable national holiday (<em>feriado nacional inamovible</em>).
          </p>
          <p>
            Official commemorations usually center on Tucumán and the <a href="https://www.argentina.gob.ar/capital-humano/cultura/monumentos/museo-casa-historica-de-la-independencia" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Casa Histórica</a>: Te Deum, flag raising, civic-military parade, presidential attendance in most years. Across the country people eat winter dishes, especially locro. Schools run pageants and flag ceremonies. Argentina also keeps 25 May (the May Revolution of 1810) as a major patriotic holiday; the two dates are often mentioned together and sometimes mixed up (<a href="https://www.lanacion.com.ar/lifestyle/por-que-recordamos-mas-revolucion-mayo-nid2265816/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">La Nación</a>). Historian <a href="https://www.lanacion.com.ar/cultura/25-de-mayo-preguntas-y-respuestas-para-entender-los-sucesos-de-una-semana-historica-nid19052021/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Daniel Balmaceda</a> puts the difference as autonomy in 1810 versus independence and sovereignty in 1816.
          </p>
          <p>
            The rest of this page covers how the declaration came about, who was included and excluded, how neighboring countries remember the same revolutionary cycle, when independence was recognized abroad, how the holiday changed afterward and common mix-ups. Later governments reused 9 July for their own projects (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bernardino_Rivadavia" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Rivadavia</a> 1826, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Juan_Manuel_de_Rosas" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Rosas</a> 1835, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Juan_Per%C3%B3n" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Perón</a> 1947, Operativo Independencia 1975, recent administrations). The Casa Histórica itself was mostly demolished in 1903–04 and reconstructed in 1943.
          </p>
          <figure class="article-figure">
